   - Uses `MATCH` to find the row of the same city in the Source 2 block (`$B$8:$B$10`).
   - Uses `INDEX` to retrieve each of the five numeric values from `$C$8:$G$10`.
   - Compares each retrieved value to the corresponding cell in the current row.
   - Wraps the whole `AND` in `IFERROR(...,FALSE)`.
3. Do the symmetric operation for Source 2 rows (rows 8‑10) looking up in `$C$3:$G$5`.
